-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Dana Gas and Industries Qatar Were Active
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-01-05T11:00:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/persian-gulf-stocks-dana-gas-and-industries-qatar-were-active.html
Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI) 
decreased 0.7 percent, the most since Dec. 21, to 2,398.76 at
the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. The measure dropped 0.2 percent
this week. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 0.2 percent while
Saudi Arabia’s market was closed for the weekend.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Dana Gas PJSC (DANA)   fell the most in more than a week,
losing 2.2 percent to 44 fils. The company after a board meeting
failed to provide details on how it plans to repay $1 billion of
Islamic bonds due in October.  Industries Qatar QSC (IQCD QD), the Middle East’s second-
biggest petrochemicals company, dropped the most since Dec. 19,
retreating 0.6 percent to 134.1 riyals. Crude for February
delivery declined as much as 0.9 percent to $102.29 a barrel on
the  New York Mercantile Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
